				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Cas=
ino game of chance</div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">This article=
 is about the casino game. For other uses, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Roulette_(disambiguation)" class=3D"mw-disambig" title=3D"Roul=
ette (disambiguation)">Roulette (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<p class=3D"mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:13-02-27-spielbank-wiesbaden-by-RalfR-094.jpg=
" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wi=
kipedia/commons/thumb/5/5d/13-02-27-spielbank-wiesbaden-by-RalfR-094.jpg/25=
0px-13-02-27-spielbank-wiesbaden-by-RalfR-094.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=
=3D"250" height=3D"166" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"4288" =
data-file-height=3D"2848"></a><figcaption>Roulette ball</figcaption></figur=
e>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Gwendolen_Harleth.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-descr=
iption"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/=
3f/Gwendolen_Harleth.jpg/250px-Gwendolen_Harleth.jpg" decoding=3D"async" wi=
dth=3D"190" height=3D"284" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"137=
2" data-file-height=3D"2050"></a><figcaption>"Gwendolen at the roulette tab=
le" =E2=80=93 1910 illustration to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/George_Eliot" title=3D"George Eliot">George Eliot</a>'s <i><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_Deronda" title=3D"Daniel Deronda">Daniel D=
eronda</a></i></figcaption></figure>
<p><b>Roulette</b> (named after the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/French_language" title=3D"French language">French</a> word meaning "littl=
e wheel") is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casino" title=3D"Ca=
sino">casino</a> game which was likely developed from the <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy" title=3D"Italy">Italian</a> game <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biribi" title=3D"Biribi">Biribi</a>. In the g=
ame, a player may choose to place a bet on a single number, various groupin=
gs of numbers, the color red or black, whether the number is odd or even, o=
r if the number is high or low.
</p><p>To determine the winning number, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Croupier" title=3D"Croupier">croupier</a> spins a wheel in one dire=
ction, then spins a ball in the opposite direction around a tilted circular=
 track running around the outer edge of the wheel. The ball eventually lose=
s <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Momentum" title=3D"Momentum">mom=
entum</a>, passes through an area of deflectors, and falls onto the wheel a=
nd into one of the colored and numbered pockets on the wheel. The winnings =
are then paid to anyone who has placed a successful bet.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"History">History</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DRoulette&amp;action=3D=
edit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit</span></a>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:EO_Wheel.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><=
img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/76/EO_Wheel.jp=
g/250px-EO_Wheel.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"190" height=3D"273" class=
=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"1171" data-file-height=3D"1685"></a=
><figcaption>18th-century E.O. wheel with gamblers</figcaption></figure>
<p>The first form of roulette was devised in 18th-century <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France" title=3D"France">France</a>. Many historian=
s believe <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blaise_Pascal" title=3D"=
Blaise Pascal">Blaise Pascal</a> introduced a primitive form of roulette in=
 the 17th century in his search for a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Perpetual_motion_machine" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Perpetual moti=
on machine">perpetual motion machine</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roulette#cite_note-1"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup> The roulette mechanism is a hybrid of a gaming wheel invented in 17=
20 and the Italian game <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biribi" ti=
tle=3D"Biribi">Biribi</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-2" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roulette#cite_note-2"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> A primi=
tive form of roulette, known as "EO" (Even/Odd), was played in England in t=
he late 18th century using a gaming wheel similar to that used in roulette.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Roulette#cite_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The game has been played in its present form since as early as 1796 =
in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris" title=3D"Paris">Paris</a=
>. An early description of the roulette game in its current form is found i=
n a French novel <i>La Roulette, ou le Jour</i> by Jaques Lablee, which des=
cribes a roulette wheel in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pal=
ais_Royal" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Palais Royal">Palais Royal</a> in=
 Paris in 1796. The description included the house pockets: "There are exac=
tly two slots reserved for the bank, whence it derives its sole mathematica=
l advantage." It then goes on to describe the layout with "two betting spac=
es containing the bank's two numbers, zero and double zero". The book was p=
ublished in 1801. An even earlier reference to a game of this name was publ=
ished in regulations for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Franc=
e" title=3D"New France">New France</a> (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Qu%C3%A9bec" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Qu=C3=A9bec">Qu=C3=A9bec<=
/a>) in 1758, which banned the games of "dice, hoca, <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Faro_(banking_game)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Faro=
 (banking game)">faro</a>, and roulette".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roulette#cite_note-4"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
</p><p>The roulette wheels used in the casinos of Paris in the late 1790s h=
ad red for the single zero and black for the double zero. To avoid confusio=
n, the color green was selected for the zeros in roulette wheels starting i=
n the 1800s.
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Flemish_characters_by_James_Gillray_(2).jpg" =
class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wiki=
pedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Flemish_characters_by_James_Gillray_%282%29.jpg/25=
0px-Flemish_characters_by_James_Gillray_%282%29.jpg" decoding=3D"async" wid=
th=3D"250" height=3D"167" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"2400=
" data-file-height=3D"1604"></a><figcaption> A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Caricature" title=3D"Caricature">caricature</a> by <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Gillray" title=3D"James Gillray">James =
Gillray</a>, 1822</figcaption></figure>
<p>In 1843, in the German spa casino town of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Bad_Homburg" title=3D"Bad Homburg">Bad Homburg</a>, fellow Frenc=
hmen <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fran%C3%A7ois_and_Louis_Blanc=
" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Fran=C3=A7ois and Louis Blanc">Fran=C3=A7o=
is and Louis Blanc</a> introduced the single <i>0</i> style roulette wheel =
in order to compete against other casinos offering the traditional wheel wi=
th single and double zero house pockets.
</p><p>In some forms of early American roulette wheels, there were numbers =
1 to 28, plus a single zero, a double zero, and an American Eagle. The Eagl=
e slot, which was a symbol of American liberty, was a house slot that broug=
ht the casino an extra edge. Soon, the tradition vanished and since then th=
e wheel features only numbered slots. According to Hoyle "the single 0, the=
 double 0, and the eagle are never bars; but when the ball falls into eithe=
r of them, the banker sweeps every thing upon the table, except what may ha=
ppen to be bet on either one of them, when he pays twenty-seven for one, wh=
ich is the amount paid for all sums bet upon any single figure".<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ro=
ulette#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-halign-left" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:1800_French_Roulette_Table_001.jpg" class=3D"m=
w-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/comm=
ons/thumb/9/9a/1800_French_Roulette_Table_001.jpg/250px-1800_French_Roulett=
e_Table_001.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"129" class=3D"m=
w-file-element" data-file-width=3D"1514" data-file-height=3D"779"></a><figc=
aption>1800s engraving of the French roulette</figcaption></figure>
<p>In the 19th century, roulette spread all over Europe and the US, becomin=
g one of the most popular casino games. When the German government abolishe=
d gambling in the 1860s, the Blanc family moved to the last legal remaining=
 casino operation in Europe at <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mon=
te_Carlo" title=3D"Monte Carlo">Monte Carlo</a>, where they established a g=
ambling mecca for the elite of Europe. It was here that the single zero rou=
lette wheel became the premier game, and over the years was exported around=
 the world, except in the United States where the double zero wheel remaine=
d dominant.
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Early_Western_Makeshift_Game.jpg" class=3D"mw=
-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/th=
umb/d/d3/Early_Western_Makeshift_Game.jpg/330px-Early_Western_Makeshift_Gam=
e.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"280" height=3D"165" class=3D"mw-file-ele=
ment" data-file-width=3D"1334" data-file-height=3D"786"></a><figcaption>Ear=
ly American West makeshift game</figcaption></figure>
<p>In the United States, the French double zero wheel made its way up the <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mississippi" title=3D"Mississippi">=
Mississippi</a> from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Orleans" =
title=3D"New Orleans">New Orleans</a>, and then westward. It was here, beca=
use of rampant cheating by both operators and gamblers, that the wheel was =
eventually placed on top of the table to prevent devices from being hidden =
in the table or wheel, and the betting layout was simplified. This eventual=
ly evolved into the American-style roulette game. The American game was dev=
eloped in the gambling dens across the new territories where makeshift game=
s had been set up, whereas the French game evolved with style and leisure i=
n Monte Carlo.
</p><p>During the first part of the 20th century, the only casino towns of =
note were Monte Carlo with the traditional single zero French wheel, and <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Las_Vegas_Valley" title=3D"Las Vegas=
 Valley">Las Vegas</a> with the American double zero wheel. In the 1970s, c=
asinos began to flourish around the world. In 1996 the first online casino,=
 generally believed to be <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/InterCas=
ino" title=3D"InterCasino">InterCasino</a>, made it possible to play roulet=
te online.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Roulette#cite_note-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> By 2008, there were sev=
eral hundred casinos worldwide offering roulette games. The double zero whe=
el is found in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States" =
title=3D"United States">United States</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Canada" title=3D"Canada">Canada</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/South_America" title=3D"South America">South America</a>, and t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caribbean" title=3D"Caribbean">=
Caribbean</a>, while the single zero wheel is predominant elsewhere.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Rules_of_play_against_a_cas=
ino">Rules of play against a casino</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/w/index.php?title=3DRoulette&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=
=3D"Edit section: Rules of play against a casino"><span>edit</span></a><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-halign-left" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Roulette_wheel.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-descripti=
on"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/R=
oulette_wheel.jpg/250px-Roulette_wheel.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"220=
" height=3D"153" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"921" data-fil=
e-height=3D"639"></a><figcaption>Roulette with red 12 as the winner</figcap=
tion></figure>
<p>Roulette players have a variety of betting options. "Inside" bets involv=
e selecting either the exact number on which the ball will land, or a small=
 group of numbers adjacent to each other on the layout. "Outside" bets, by =
contrast, allow players to select a larger group of numbers based on proper=
ties such as their color or parity (odd/even). The payout odds for each typ=
e of bet are based on its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probabil=
ity" title=3D"Probability">probability</a>.
</p><p>The roulette table usually imposes minimum and maximum bets, and the=
se rules usually apply separately for all of a player's inside and outside =
bets for each spin. For inside bets at roulette tables, some casinos may us=
e separate roulette table chips of various colors to distinguish players at=
 the table. Players can continue to place bets as the ball spins around the=
 wheel until the dealer announces "no more bets" or "rien ne va plus".
</p>
<figure typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/F=
ile:13-02-27-spielbank-wiesbaden-by-RalfR-085.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-descrip=
tion"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74=
/13-02-27-spielbank-wiesbaden-by-RalfR-085.jpg/250px-13-02-27-spielbank-wie=
sbaden-by-RalfR-085.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"220" height=3D"146" cl=
ass=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"4288" data-file-height=3D"2848">=
</a><figcaption>Croupier's rake pushing chips across a roulette layout</fig=
caption></figure>
<p>When a winning number and color is determined by the roulette wheel, the=
 dealer will place a marker, also known as a <i>dolly</i>, on that number o=
n the roulette table layout. When the dolly is on the table, no players may=
 place bets, collect bets or remove any bets from the table. The dealer wil=
l then sweep away all losing bets either by hand or by rake, and determine =
the payouts for the remaining inside and outside winning bets. When the dea=
ler is finished making payouts, the dolly is removed from the board and pla=
yers may collect their winnings and make new bets. Winning chips remain on =
the board until picked up by a player.=20
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"California_Roulette">Califo=
rnia Roulette</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DRoulette&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Calif=
ornia Roulette"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<p>In 2004, California legalized a form of roulette known as California Rou=
lette.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Roulette#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> By law, the game must use c=
ards and not slots on the roulette wheel to pick the winning number.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Roulette_wheel_number_seque=
nce">Roulette wheel number sequence</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/w/index.php?title=3DRoulette&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=
=3D"Edit section: Roulette wheel number sequence"><span>edit</span></a><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The pockets of the roulette wheel are numbered from 0 to 36.
</p><p>In number ranges from 1 to 10 and 19 to 28, odd numbers are red and =
even are black. In ranges from 11 to 18 and 29 to 36, odd numbers are black=
 and even are red.
</p><p>There is a green pocket numbered 0 (zero). In American roulette, the=
re is a second green pocket marked 00. Pocket number order on the roulette =
wheel adheres to the following clockwise sequence in most casinos:<sup clas=
s=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[=
<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" titl=
e=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs references =
to reliable sources. (August 2011)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p>
<dl><dt>Single-zero wheel</dt>
<dd>0-32-15-19-4-21-2-25-17-34-6-27-13-36-11-30-8-23-10-5-24-16-33-1-20-14-=
31-9-22-18-29-7-28-12-35-3-26</dd>
<dt>Double-zero wheel</dt>
<dd>0-28-9-26-30-11-7-20-32-17-5-22-34-15-3-24-36-13-1-00-27-10-25-29-12-8-=
19-31-18-6-21-33-16-4-23-35-14-2</dd>
<dt>Triple-zero wheel</dt>
<dd>0-000-00-32-15-19-4-21-2-25-17-34-6-27-13-36-11-30-8-23-10-5-24-16-33-1=
-20-14-31-9-22-18-29-7-28-12-35-3-26</dd></dl>
