</td>
<td>On the outer corner shared by 0-1 or 00-3
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Outside_bets">Outside bets<=
/h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DRoulette&amp=
;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Outside bets"><span>=
edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Outside bets typically have smaller payouts with better odds at winning.=
 Except as noted, all of these bets lose if a 0 comes up.
</p>
<dl><dt>1 to 18 (low or <i>manque</i>), or 19 to 36 (high or <i>passe</i>)<=
/dt>
<dd>A bet that the number will be in the chosen range.</dd>
<dt>Red or black (<i>rouge ou noir</i>)</dt>
<dd>A bet that the number will be the chosen color.</dd>
<dt>Even or odd (<i>pair ou impair</i>)</dt>
<dd>A bet that the number will be of the chosen <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Parity_(mathematics)" title=3D"Parity (mathematics)">parity</=
a>. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parity_of_0" class=3D"mw-redir=
ect" title=3D"Parity of 0">
Unlike in mathematics</a>, in Roulette 0 is considered neither even nor odd=
.</dd>
<dt>Dozen bet</dt>
<dd>A bet that the number will be in the chosen dozen: first (1-12, <i>Prem=
i=C3=A8re douzaine</i> or P12), second (13-24, <i>Moyenne douzaine</i> or M=
12), or third (25-36, <i>Derni=C3=A8re douzaine</i> or D12).</dd>
<dt>Column bet</dt>
<dd>A bet that the number will be in the chosen vertical column of 12 numbe=
rs, such as 1-4-7-10 on down to 34. The chip is placed on the space below t=
he final number in this sequence.</dd>
<dt>Snake bet</dt>
<dd>A special bet that covers the numbers 1, 5, 9, 12, 14, 16, 19, 23, 27, =
30, 32, and 34. It has the same payout as the dozen bet and takes its name =
from the zig-zagging, snakelike pattern traced out by these numbers. The sn=
ake bet is not available in all casinos; when it is allowed, the chip is pl=
aced on the lower corner of the 34 square that borders the 19-36 betting bo=
x. Some layouts mark the bet with a two-headed snake that winds from 1 to 3=
4, and the bet can be placed on the head at either end of the body.</dd></d=
l>
<p>In some casinos, the farthest outside bets (low/high, red/black, even/od=
d) result in the player losing only half of their bet if a zero comes up. T=
his is known as the "halfback" or <i>la partage</i> rule. Others may use an=
 "imprisonment" or <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/En_prison" t=
itle=3D"En prison">en prison</a></i> rule, wherein a loss on such an outsid=
e bet causes the player's money to be "imprisoned", and if the next spin wo=
uld be a win for that bet, the player's wager is returned.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Bet_odds_table">Bet odds ta=
ble</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DRoulette=
&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit section: Bet odds table">=
<span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>=
</div>
<p>The expected value of a $1 bet (except for the special case of top line =
bets), for American and European roulette, can be calculated as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\text{expected value}}=3D{\frac {1}{n}}(36-n)=3D{\frac {36}{n}}-1,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mtext>expected value</mtext>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mn>36</mn>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>36</mn>
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\text{expect=
ed value}}=3D{\frac {1}{n}}(36-n)=3D{\frac {36}{n}}-1,}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/1f0b84f180be08889fe8844f6f7872815d7b3650" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:39.397ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
text{expected value}}=3D{\frac {1}{n}}(36-n)=3D{\frac {36}{n}}-1,}"></span>=
</dd></dl>
<p>where <i>n</i> is the number of pockets in the wheel.
</p><p>The initial bet is returned in addition to the mentioned payout: it =
can be easily demonstrated that this payout formula would lead to a zero <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expected_value" title=3D"Expected va=
lue">expected value</a> of profit if there were only 36 numbers (that is, t=
he casino would break even). Having 37 or more numbers gives the casino its=
 edge.
</p>
